snippet.textDisplay:
Just in case anyone is still looking for the seams on this:


- Michaels camera crossfades into another shot
- That shot then gets sped up at 4:08 to make it look like the cart is moving "fast"
- The cockpit shot doesn´t line up with the "speedup" AND it just cuts out at the crucial moment
- at 4:09 is propably the direct cut - look at this sky as it changes exposure from one frame to the next
- The "fire" is ridiculously close to the camera for the cameraguy to be so unfazed by it OR nothing happening with exposure or some kind of haze/whatever on the lens
- The "fire" doesn´t move with the camera but stays in one position. Because it was added in post.
- and uhm IT BLOCKS the screen for TWO SECONDS so you cant see anything, nice "trick"

snippet.textDisplay:
That was absolutely amazing!!! Dude, I’ve never seen anything like that! Other magicians aren’t even in your league, my ninja. Don’t listen to them haters, they just jelly. I’m legit blown away! I usually don’t like ‘magic’ shows, but this was fire, helicopters, crazy fast little car, and Houdini here jumping into a jail cell at 50 ft in the air going hella fast!! Then Boom!!! I was like no way! This dude’s in the cell! Like no way, bro! I can’t believe it! It was one camera, continuously w/out edits. I watched it over and over, and I think I know some of your secrets, but it’s only because I have a really high IQ. I notice stuff. I’m pretty sure you’re doing something when the car goes up the ramp, right before the explosion. I think there’s hologramic evidence that you used a hologram but I also think the car turns into the cell, but not all of it. So, you’re using the sun directly focusing dead center of the horizon but not accounting for refraction. So, it looks perpendicular to ongoing traffic, but towards the vanishing point, not above the cringe. I can’t imagine how you used the rest of that on coffee and cigarettes, but it wasn’t long enough before what began as something small finally happened!! I could not believe
I rose and ran towards the television with a reckless abandon I’d not known in years, and from the looks of it, the brunt of time hath taken it’s wage from my constitution. Oh yeah, that’s the stuff!!
